com.dxfeed.model

Class AbstractIndexedEventModel.Entry<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dxfeed.model.AbstractIndexedEventModel.Entry<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of events.
    Enclosing class:
    AbstractIndexedEventModel<E extends IndexedEvent<?>,N extends AbstractIndexedEventModel.Entry<E>>

    public static class AbstractIndexedEventModel.Entry<V>
extends Object
    Represents an internal entry in the model. It can be extended to add additional state to the entry.
    See Also:
    AbstractIndexedEventModel.createEntry()

    • Method Detail

      • getValue

        public V getValue()
        Returns current values of the entry. During AbstractIndexedEventModel.modelChanged it is the value before the change, until commitChange() method is invoked.
        Returns:
        current values of the entry.

      • getNewValue

        public V getNewValue()
        Returns new value of the entry, after the most recent change, null if the element is removed from the model. It can differ from value only during AbstractIndexedEventModel.modelChanged method invocation and until commitChange() method is invoked.
        Returns:
        new value of the entry, after the most recent change.

      • isChanged

        public boolean isChanged()
        Returns true if the value was updated and in the most recent change. It is set to true only during AbstractIndexedEventModel.modelChanged method invocation and until commitChange() method is invoked.
        Returns:
        true if the value was updated and in the most recent change.

      • commitChange

        public void commitChange()
        Commits the most recent change by copying newValue to current value and clearing changed flag, if it was not cleared yet.
